  "notes": {
    "345ec2cb736b619c26b5e443dc6c96d9_x0": "A and D are the clearest for a non-specialist reader. Terms like 'Blockältester' need more explanation in all candidates. F is well-written but assumes familiarity with camp hierarchy. B and C's first-person framing is confusing—it's unclear who is speaking.",
    "345ec2cb736b619c26b5e443dc6c96d9_x1": "C and E are the most accessible. F is confusing—raises perpetrator possibility without explaining why, which is alarming without context. 'Kapos' and 'Aussenkommandos' go unexplained in most versions. B is careful but somewhat dry.",
    "345ec2cb736b619c26b5e443dc6c96d9_x2": "This record produced the clearest candidates overall—perhaps because the source itself is more descriptive. B, C, D, and F are all excellent and immediately comprehensible. The quantitative details (300g bread, 14-15 hours) make the suffering concrete and accessible.",
    "345ec2cb736b619c26b5e443dc6c96d9_x3": "B is the most helpful because it explains 'Anschluss'—most others assume you know what the 'occupation of Vienna' refers to. D is also good narratively. The source is confusing about who murdered whom, and most candidates inherit this confusion.",
    "345ec2cb736b619c26b5e443dc6c96d9_x4": "F is the clearest and most direct—no hedging that obscures the message. The 'Rath campaign' is left unexplained by all candidates, which is a gap for non-specialists. D is also strong. E's academic hedging makes it harder to follow."
  }
